%S A392962 1,1,1,2,1,3,6,6,7,5,9,15,18,19,23,26,23,34,39,42,45,48,60,65,79
%N A392962 Number of automorphism group orders that occur for exactly one unlabeled tree with n vertices.
%C A392962 Let T(n) be the set of all unlabeled trees with n vertices. For each tree T in T(n), let Aut(T) be its automorphism group and |Aut(T)| its order.
%C A392962 For each integer m, define f(n, m) = number of trees T in T(n) such that |Aut(T)| = m. Then a(n) is the number of integers m such that f(n, m) = 1. Equivalently, a(n) counts those automorphism group orders that occur exactly once among all unlabeled trees with n vertices.
%C A392962 Compare with A391694, which counts all distinct orders without regard to multiplicity.
%H A392962 Igor Blokhin, <a href="https://github.com/IgorBlokhin/Graph-Theory">Graph theory</a> (Python repository)
%e A392962 n = 5: There are three unlabeled trees with automorphism group orders 24, 2, 2. Only 24 occurs exactly once. Hence a(5) = 1.
%Y A392962 Cf. A000055, A391694.
